\nshown that the proposed generalized impedance flow method accurately captures\nthe shear shock wave motion. This method can lead to improvements in image\nsequence design that takes into account the aberration and multiple reflections\nfrom the brain and in the design of tracking algorithms that can more\naccurately capture the complex brain motion that occurs during a traumatic\nimpact.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Mar 2020 19:00:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-17"}
