iedmann-Lemaitre-Robertson-Walker (FLRW) metric has ${\\cal\nC}(z) \\equiv 0$; thus, measurement of the CBL function could provide another\ndiagnostic of torsion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 14 Mar 2020 01:15:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-04"}
